flowRoot.flowPara: Verify that all parts of the return shipping pack are present, as listed below. Also, verify that you have all of the parts to be returned, as specified by your Student Robotics contact. If either parts of this pack or parts to be returned are missing, please get in touch.
1× polythene bag, 5× cable ties, 1× LiPo warning label, 2× document wallets, 1× brown paper, 4x brown jiffy bags, 4x white jiffy bags

Place all parts to be returned, except for cables, into the jiffy bags. If returning a tablet, please place that in its own white bag and if returning batteries, place them together into their own brown bag. Place any small/loose parts, such as WiFi dongles, USB memory sticks, pluggable terminal blocks (camcons), into a single brown jiffy bag and seal it.
Please do not overfill or seal any of the bags other than the one containing loose items.
If returning batteries, please place the brown jiffy bag that they are contained in into the battery charging bag.
Tear the brown paper into two equal sized pieces and loosely scrunch them up to make them more voluminous. Place one of these pieces of brown paper into the bottom of the Really Useful Box.
Place all of the jiffy bags, the battery charging bag (if returning batteries) and all cables on top of the layer of brown paper. Then place the second piece of scrunched up brown paper on top.

Working on one end of the lid at a time, pass a cable tie through the two holes, from the inside to the outside. Fold the block end of the two cable ties under the lip of the lid and place the lid on the box such that both ends of the cable ties are outside of the box. Feed the non-block ends of the cable ties through the holes in the handle and clip the handle shut. Loosely zip up the cable ties. Repeat this procedure for the other end of the lid. Now zip up all four cable ties tightly, with their tails pointing straight down the side of the box. Please do not cut off the tails as the sharp corners can damage the polythene bag.

Place the box into the polythene bag and seal it shut using the built in adhesive strip and extra tape over the flap. If the box contains batteries, stick the LiPo warning label onto the package. Stick one of the document pouches onto the package, taking care to leave the narrow backing strip in place until you have put the shipping label in.

If you are organising the courier, now is the time to book the collection and obtain a shipping label. If we are organising the courier, please notify your Student Robotics contact that the package is wrapped and we will provide you with a shipping label. Place the shipping label into the document pouch and seal it by removing the narrow strip. Finally, hand the package to reception or wherever it will be collected from and notify your contact.
